			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001020_0001"/><!--pb/@n='191-1'-->
<addSpan spanTo="#p.191-1" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left margin of fol. 191-1'--></addSpan>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">The Portuguese Government has 
<lb/>ordered my men to be supported by <placeName>Mosambique 
<lb/>Province</placeName></p><anchor xml:id="p.191-1"/>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>57 Sloane St</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">16<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857</p>
<lb/><p>Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>I fully 
<lb/>intended to accept 
<lb/>your very kind 
<lb/>invitation today 
<lb/>but I feel for 
<lb/>the first time 
<lb/>since I came home 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001020_0002"/><!--pb/@n='191a-2'--> 
<lb/>the effects of 
<lb/>overwork in 
<lb/>great lassitude 
<lb/>and a feeling 
<lb/>of illness. I attended 
<lb/>the Anniversary 
<lb/>of the <term type="organisation">London 
<lb/>Missionary Society</term>
<lb/>on Thursday and 
<lb/>have hurt my 
<lb/>throat in trying 
<lb/>to speechify to 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001020_0003"/><!--pb/@n='191a-3'--> 
<lb/>upwards of 2000 
<lb/>people a work 
<lb/>for which I 
<lb/>have always 
<lb/>believed I was 
<lb/>never intended<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>It is not the speaking 
<lb/>so much as the 
<lb/>sitting sweating 
<lb/>in agony about 
<lb/>what you will 
<lb/>say for hours 
<lb/>beforehand. I would 
<lb/>be ashamed to 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001020_0004"/><!--pb/@n='191-4'--> 
<lb/>meet <persName>Lady Hooker</persName>
<lb/>in this state so I 
<lb/>now (4 O clock) 
<lb/>beg you to allow 
<lb/>me to come next 
<lb/><add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">Friday or</add> Saturday instead 
<lb/><del type="strikethrough">of this</del><reg>.</reg> We shall 
<lb/>be sure to come 
<lb/>on either the one 
<lb/>day or the other<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Please do not trouble 
<lb/>yourself to write 
<lb/>again, but accept 
<lb/>my hearty thanks 
<lb/>for the invitation<reg>.</reg> D. Livingstone</p> 			
</div>
